sub_title: Data Scientist / Quantitative Marketing Manager at Digital Marketing at KLM Royal Dutch Airlines
summary:
Data Scientist / Quantitative Marketing Manager

Deep Reinforcement Learning, Probabilistic Deep Learning, Bayesian Structural Time Series, Evolutionary Computation.

Google Cloud Platform, Kubernetes, Terraform, Docker, GitHub Actions, Kubeflow, Vertex AI, Power BI.

Relay42, TIBCO Spotfire.

Skill Profile - https://github.com/maxvol/CV
Coursera certificates - https://github.com/maxvol/Coursera
DataCamp certificates - https://github.com/maxvol/DataCamp

* In airline business since 2008.
* Data scientist & machine learning engineer since 2018.
* Mobile developer since 2011.
* Web developer since 1999.
* Software developer since 1996.

Mobile App Developer / Team Lead

I am ranked as "Top-5 Swift Developer Netherlands" by CodersRank (https://profile.codersrank.io/user/maxvol/).

I provided talks on Reactive app development with RxJava (for "Reactive Amsterdam" and "Dutch Android User Group" developer communities) and RxSwift (for "Swift User Group Netherlands").

I am active on GitHub (https://github.com/maxvol) and StackOverflow (https://stackoverflow.com/users/856588/maxim-volgin). Member/contributor of RxSwiftCommunity, author/maintainer of RxCloudKit, RxARKit, RxSceneKit, RxSpriteKit, RxOnDemandResources, RxCoreNFC, GeoJSONMap, and several other frameworks.

I have several personal apps in AppStore (https://itunes.apple.com/nl/developer/m-volgin/id1078541197).

I also write technical articles on Medium (https://medium.com/@maxim.volgin).

Professional software developer/engineer since 1996.
Programming languages: 1995-2002 C/C++, 1997-2018 Java/J2EE, 2010-2015 Objective-C, 2014-now Swift, 2017-now Kotlin, 2018-now Python.

Agile/Scrum practitioner.

Specialties: Rx, RxJava, RxKotlin, RxSwift
RxDataSources, RxCoreData, RxCloudKit, RxCoreLocation, RxVision, Vision, ARKit, CoreML
BSD, Linux, macOS, iOS, Android
cryptography and security in iOS and Java
BLE, IoT, LBS, ANCS, iBeacon, APN, Blockchain
TensorFlow, Scikit-Learn, TuriCreate, CreateML

Hobbies: mbed, Arduino, Raspberry Pi, BeagleBone
